 FOUR persons have been killed in a cult clash in Onueke Ezza South Local Government Area of Ebonyi State. The state government has inaugurated a local vigilance team in the area to checkmate cult activities. Commissioner for Internal Security, Border Peace and Conflict Resolution, Stanley Okoro Emegha inaugurated the team yesterday. The Commissioner urged members of the group to take their job seriously, adding that the state would not tolerate further cult clashes in the local government area or any other part of the state.   